  "soap_summary": "Patient reports 3 days of loose watery diarrhea (6-7/day) with left lower crampy abdominal pain, initial vomiting now resolved, subjective fever at onset, weakness, and loss of appetite. No blood in stool or vomit. Asthma controlled with inhaler. Likely gastroenteritis (unconfirmed). Management: hydration / oral rehydration solution, consider stool testing if not improving, paracetamol for fever/weakness, 2-3 days off work.",
